1
00:00:14,867 --> 00:00:17,200
If Red is okay and nothing
terrible happened to him.

2
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:19,167
Red and I had an argument
because of that Amanda!

3
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,733
Because Amanda...

4
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:21,767
That's enough, Rina!

5
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:23,767
If there's anyone to blame here,
it's you!

6
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:26,167
If you only had left
Amanda alone,

7
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:27,833
she wouldn't have met our son.

8
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,433
You didn't see Eden there?

9
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,167
No. She wasn't there.

10
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:33,733
Eden!

11
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,433
Are you hurt? What happened
to you?

12
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:38,667
Yenyen is nothing but a bad
influence on him.

13
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:43,733
Even on the island, she was
always causing him trouble.

14
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,600
According to what
Sabina told me,

15
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:49,933
I don't think Yenyen is a good
influence on you.

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,667
Maybe we can still work on...

17
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:54,367
Sab, if you think that just
because Yenyen and I broke up

18
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:57,833
we can easily go back to how we
were now, you're mistaken.

19
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,333
I can only offer you friendship.

20
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,700
You must be forcing yourself
on him again.

21
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:03,200
You're making yourself
look dumb.

22
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,533
The nerve of you to call me
dumb.

23
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,133
When I'm one of the honor
students in this campus.

24
00:01:08,233 --> 00:01:10,267
But you're just a good swimmer!

25
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,367
Haven't you learned your lesson?

26
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:15,233
You're doing the same thing
again and again.

27
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,567
You have to do a reality check,
Sabina.

28
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:21,333
It will be better if you tell
her the truth yourself.

29
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:24,500
I know your mom won't be able
to accept it right away.

30
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:27,400
But it will be more painful
if she finds the truth

31
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:29,733
from someone else.

32
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,967
You have to stop
before it's too late.

33
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:35,867
If you can't fight
for your relationship.

34
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:52,067
What are you doing here?

35
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:55,000
I saw you with Yenyen earlier.

36
00:01:55,067 --> 00:01:57,867
It didn't seem like you were
trying to avoid her.

37
00:01:57,933 --> 00:01:59,467
So what's the deal?

38
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:01,700
Were you lying to me?

39
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:03,900
I thought you didn't like liars?

40
00:02:03,967 --> 00:02:06,900
Sab, whatever I have going on
with Yenyen,

41
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:08,200
you have nothing to do with it.

42
00:02:08,267 --> 00:02:11,033
Stay out of it, please.

43
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:12,767
I have something to do with it.

44
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:31,133
Look, I really am curious
about this Yenyen girl.

45
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:34,467
Now Sabina has told me
a lot about her.

46
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:39,867
But then again, if she's the
girl you like, then so be it.

47
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:42,333
I won't stop you
from liking her.

48
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,067
What?

49
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,567
Look, Red.

50
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:49,500
I cannot control your feelings,
okay?

51
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:54,400
You are old enough to decide
who you want.

52
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:57,800
Just don't lie to me.

53
00:02:57,867 --> 00:03:04,267
Now tell me, what is so special
about this Yenyen girl?

54
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,167
Do you need anything?

55
00:03:14,233 --> 00:03:19,800
Mom...

56
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:23,600
Our tournament is about
to begin.

57
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:28,867
I might get busy, so I just want
to let you know.

58
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:33,933
I might come home late these
coming days.

59
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,400
Okay, I understand.

60
00:03:36,467 --> 00:03:38,067
Be careful.

61
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:50,233
Eden...

62
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:56,100
I know we've been apart
for a long time.

63
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,800
And you became closer
with your Aunt Dindi.

64
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:01,500
Because...

65
00:04:01,567 --> 00:04:05,867
you two were together
while I'm gone.

66
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:10,833
Eden, you sometimes feel
awkward around me, right?

67
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:17,067
But I'm your mom.

68
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:18,367
I'm here now.

69
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:23,567
I hope you won't feel
embarrassed to open up to me.

70
00:04:25,267 --> 00:04:30,300
Don't hesitate to share
your secret with me

71
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:33,467
or any unpleasant feelings.

72
00:04:33,533 --> 00:04:34,400
Okay?

73
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:55,200
This is your chance to tell me
the truth.

74
00:04:58,333 --> 00:04:59,967
Nothing, Mom.

75
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:03,067
Well, we're still friends.

76
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:06,067
When she tripped at the gym,
I only helped her up...

77
00:05:06,133 --> 00:05:09,333
like how she helped me
while we were on the island.

78
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,467
That's all there is to it.

79
00:05:10,533 --> 00:05:11,967
But, why do I feel that...

80
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:15,333
Then you're wrong.

81
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:18,367
Yenyen and I are just friends.

82
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:21,100
Excuse me, guys. I'm tired.
I need to rest.

83
00:05:21,167 --> 00:05:22,200
Okay.

84
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:26,400
Auntie, are you serious?

85
00:05:26,467 --> 00:05:30,733
Are you going to push that
Yenyen to be with Red?

86
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:35,067
I cannot control his feelings.

87
00:05:35,167 --> 00:05:38,267
If he likes her, then I can't do
anything about it.

88
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:47,000
Now, instead of wasting
your time hovering over him...

89
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:51,300
If you really want to do
something about it,

90
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:53,100
then do something about it.

91
00:05:53,167 --> 00:05:55,400
So you can get back together.

92
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:58,033
Auntie, I'm doing everything
I can.

93
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:03,067
But it's not working.

94
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:04,933
Try harder.

95
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:04,233
Eden, someone's calling
your phone.

96
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:10,400
Eden, should I answer it?
It could be important.

97
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,333
Hello?

98
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,533
Who is this?

99
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,567
This is Eden's mom.

100
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:32,033
Hello?

101
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,633
Who is this?

102
00:07:36,167 --> 00:07:37,600
What do you want
from my daughter?

103
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:39,200
Who is this?

104
00:07:54,567 --> 00:07:56,567
Mom, who was that?

105
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:57,700
I don't know.

106
00:07:57,767 --> 00:07:59,700
He didn't answer.

107
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:02,267
There's no name on the caller.

108
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:04,700
It's just a blue heart.

109
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,733
Who's that?

110
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:10,233
It's Blue, my classmate.

111
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:13,167
Maybe he's shy that's why
he didn't respond.

112
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:15,467
I'll just call her back.

113
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,233
Excuse me, Mom.

114
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:26,433
Hello?

115
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:30,567
Didn't I tell you to text me
first before calling?

116
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:34,133
My mom might recognize
your voice.

117
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,433
I'm sorry.

118
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:39,433
I just want to tell you that Sab
is spying on us.

119
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:47,867
You know, we really need to be
careful.

120
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:50,900
I just realized it earlier
while talking to my mom.

121
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:54,867
I tried to tell her the truth,
but I couldn't do it.

122
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,167
We just need to sacrifice
a little more.

123
00:09:00,233 --> 00:09:02,900
We need to endure this, okay?

124
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:07,867
Red, I don't think
I can do this much longer.

125
00:09:07,933 --> 00:09:09,633
I'm afraid of what could happen.

126
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,767
Do you want to meet tomorrow?

127
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:20,300
Let's talk about our plan.

128
00:09:20,367 --> 00:09:24,500
Let's meet at Cafe Polca
around 2 pm?

129
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:25,933
I'll see you there?

130
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:31,033
Okay, see you.

131
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:01,867
Did Eden tell you something?

132
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:04,767
About what?

133
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:07,933
I don't know.

134
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,867
Didn't she say anything?

135
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:16,200
I just noticed that she's acting
weird lately.

136
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:23,200
Maybe you're just
not used to her yet.

137
00:10:23,267 --> 00:10:24,367
She acts like that sometimes,

138
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:26,600
especially if she has a lot
of school activities.

139
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:28,667
Don't mind her.

140
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:55,333
Mom, I'll just ask permission.
I'm going somewhere.

141
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,667
It's Saturday.
Where are you going?

142
00:10:57,733 --> 00:11:02,100
Raichu asked me to go with her
to buy swimwear.

143
00:11:02,167 --> 00:11:06,633
Okay. Be safe.

144
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,567
Okay, Mom. Bye.

145
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,300
Bye, Auntie.

146
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,200
Stop, stop, stop.

147
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,567
Mister, follow that taxi.

148
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,033
She's on her way. She'll be here
in about five minutes.

149
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:10,733
Are you sure they have good
food here?

150
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:13,000
I need a distraction because
of what's happening

151
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:14,867
between Red and I. My God.

152
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:30,733
I'll just get whatever
you're getting.

153
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,233
Is that...

154
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,433
Is that Red?

155
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,767
What is he doing here?

156
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:50,467
Are you sure you didn't mess up?

157
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:55,167
He might tell the cops.

158
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,800
I don't want any trouble.

159
00:12:56,867 --> 00:12:59,567
With all the beating
I gave that fool,

160
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:01,400
I'm sure he learned
his lesson by now.

161
00:13:01,467 --> 00:13:04,467
He said he'd pay next week.

162
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,567
Well, he has to.

163
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:08,900
I don't want any trouble
with Mr. Akashi.

164
00:13:26,467 --> 00:13:27,633
Yes, Sabina.

165
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:29,467
What can I do for you today?

166
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,900
Auntie, I'm in a restaurant
right now.

167
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:33,167
And guess what?

168
00:13:33,233 --> 00:13:35,467
Red is here too.

169
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:38,600
And he's having
something set up.

170
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:40,667
I think he's doing this
for Yenyen.

171
00:13:40,733 --> 00:13:42,767
Is it something like a date?

172
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:43,967
Are they on a date?

173
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:45,533
Yes, Auntie.

174
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,700
I know Red.

175
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:47,967
When he's having something
set up,

176
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,400
it means there's something
special.

177
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:52,933
Why don't you come here?

178
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:57,233
So you can meet Yenyen
once and for all.

179
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:01,933
Yenyen.

180
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,467
Red, what is this?

181
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:09,200
To welcome you back to Paradise.

182
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,867
Didn't you say you wanted to go
back to the island?

183
00:14:12,933 --> 00:14:15,567
So I brought the island to you.

184
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:17,067
- Red.
- Yenyen,

185
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:19,767
no one will bother us here.

186
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,567
We'll be together.

187
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:24,167
And just be happy here.

188
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:26,267
Really?

189
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:30,200
I'm looking forward
to meeting her really.

190
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:33,600
I want to get to know
who this Yenyen is.

191
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:36,200
So they don't need to hide
their relationship from us.

192
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:37,233
Right?

193
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,867
They're hiding their
relationship.

194
00:14:39,933 --> 00:14:44,033
I'm okay with it anyway.

195
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,767
Anything that will
make my son happy.

196
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:07,133
I just want to do something
special with you.

197
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:12,467
And I just want to thank you
for giving us a second chance.

198
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:15,433
And most especially, I want to
take away your stress.

199
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,967
I know how stressed you are.

200
00:15:18,033 --> 00:15:21,400
We're going through a lot
because of our family.

201
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:26,333
By the way, this is for you.

202
00:15:28,467 --> 00:15:32,033
Red, come on. You don't need
to do this.

203
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,067
You know...

204
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:41,100
every day that I'm with you
is always special.

205
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,967
Come on, let's eat.

206
00:15:43,033 --> 00:15:43,967
Thank you, Red.

207
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:45,667
No problem, Yen.

208
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:49,367
There.

209
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:50,900
- That looks good.
- I hope you're hungry

210
00:15:50,967 --> 00:15:52,067
because they have great food
here.

211
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:56,167
I'm really starving.

212
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,700
You might be hungry.

213
00:15:57,767 --> 00:15:59,367
Is this your first time here?

214
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:18,700
Mister, can I ask you something?

215
00:16:18,767 --> 00:16:20,567
What is it?

216
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:26,467
Can you tell me where you drop
off the young lady earlier?

217
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:27,700
Where did she get off?

218
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,200
Why? Who are you?

219
00:16:29,267 --> 00:16:30,200
I'm her mom.

220
00:16:30,267 --> 00:16:31,833
We have an emergency.

221
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:34,100
My phone is dead.
I can't contact her.

222
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:35,467
- Is that so?
- Yes.

223
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:38,367
I drop her off over there,
at Cafe Polca.

224
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:39,600
- Just straight ahead?
- Yes.

225
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:41,433
Okay, thank you.

226
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:56,467
How are you?

227
00:16:56,533 --> 00:16:57,867
- Hi, Auntie.
- Hello.

228
00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:00,367
I was right. Red and Yenyen
are here.

229
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:01,433
Fantastic.

230
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,733
Oh, there she is!

231
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,867
I'm finally going to meet
Red's girlfriend.

232
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,200
Are you for real?

233
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,667
Are you going to approve it?

234
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:11,367
Of course.

235
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:17,667
Whatever makes my son happy,
I'm happy.

236
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,067
Okay.

237
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:20,333
Let's go.

238
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,200
Miss!

239
00:17:32,267 --> 00:17:34,633
Do you know where Cafe Polca is?

240
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:37,733
Over there. Go straight ahead.

241
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,033
Okay, thank you.

242
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:43,800
Thank you, Red.

243
00:17:43,867 --> 00:17:46,733
You made me happy today.

244
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,167
I'll do everything
to make you happy, Yen.

245
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:57,800
You'd been texting me
that you were starving.

246
00:17:57,867 --> 00:17:59,467
Red?

247
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,600
Mom, what are you doing here?

248
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:07,800
I'm here to meet Yenyen.

249
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,900
So, you're Yenyen?

250
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:24,767
Ma'am Rina...

251
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:26,267
Sir Victor.

252
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:28,100
I'm Eden.

253
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:30,400
I'm begging you.

254
00:18:30,467 --> 00:18:33,467
Please don't put my mom in jail.

255
00:18:33,533 --> 00:18:36,300
Remember this.

256
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:41,567
I will seek justice
for my son's death.

257
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:46,567
I will make sure your mom
will rot in jail.

258
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:49,767
I won't leave her alone.

259
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:51,867
Good afternoon, Ma'am.

260
00:18:51,933 --> 00:18:53,600
I know you!

261
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:57,900
You're a criminal's daughter!

262
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,800
This must be your daughter.

263
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:02,967
Eden, right?

264
00:19:04,667 --> 00:19:05,667
Eden?

265
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:15,533
You're Yenyen?

266
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:20,433
You're the daughter of the woman
who killed my son!

267
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,100
- Mom!
- My God!

268
00:19:22,167 --> 00:19:23,500
- Mom! Mom stop!
- You monster!

269
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:26,067
- Now you're with my other son?
- Mom stop!

270
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,567
Get away from my son!

271
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:30,567
- Get away from him!
- Mom! Don't hurt her!

272
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,600
Get out of here!

273
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:34,800
Why are you hurting my daughter?

274
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:38,533
Get your daughter away from my
son!

275
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:42,233
Mom. Me and Yenyen love each
other.

276
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:48,233
What is this boy saying?

277
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:51,200
You two are in a relationship?

278
00:19:51,267 --> 00:19:55,667
Mom...

279
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:57,433
Don't cry.

280
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:59,233
Answer me.

281
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:05,333
Red is my boyfriend, Mom.

282
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:08,700
Mom...

283
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:13,867
Come here.

284
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,433
- Come over here.
- Don't hurt her.

285
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:18,967
- Stay here.
- Stay out of this!

286
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:20,200
You too!

287
00:20:20,267 --> 00:20:22,533
Get your daughter away from my
son! Get her away!

288
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:26,133
Stay out of our business!

289
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,500
Don't get involved!

290
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:35,100
What are we still doing here?

291
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,600
Let's go home.

292
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:39,000
You have a lot to explain
to your dad and me.

293
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:41,033
Mom, I can't leave her here.

294
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,833
What are you talking about?

295
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:43,967
Come on!

296
00:20:44,033 --> 00:20:47,633
What don't you understand?

297
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:52,967
Mom, I love him.

298
00:20:53,033 --> 00:20:56,967
We love each other, Mom.

299
00:20:57,033 --> 00:21:00,333
No. That's not true.

300
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:04,033
You can't love him!

301
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:08,200
Her mom killed your brother!

302
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:10,400
Are you giving that woman
much importance?

303
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:13,667
There are plenty of women
out there!

304
00:21:13,733 --> 00:21:16,567
Don't you get that I like her,
Mom?

305
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,833
When we were on the island,
I knew that I loved her!

306
00:21:18,900 --> 00:21:19,867
- No!
- I hope you understand!

307
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:21,900
No!

308
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:29,533
You don't know the pain I felt
when your brother died.

309
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:34,367
Didn't you get hurt
when your brother died?

310
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:38,267
Why can't you understand?

311
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:42,267
She killed your brother!

312
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:43,600
Red!

313
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:44,867
I know!

314
00:21:44,933 --> 00:21:47,467
I know, okay? I was in pain too!

315
00:21:47,533 --> 00:21:50,633
You were not the only one
in pain, Mom!

316
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:53,067
And I'm sorry!

317
00:21:53,133 --> 00:21:55,033
But are you sure?

318
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:57,433
Are you sure that
she's to blame?

319
00:21:57,500 --> 00:22:00,167
We don't even know!

320
00:22:00,233 --> 00:22:02,400
What are you talking about?
What do you mean by that?

321
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,933
That woman is guilty!

322
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,467
She was put behind bars!

323
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,033
What do you think?

324
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:13,067
Did you think the court
would lie?

325
00:22:13,133 --> 00:22:14,633
But Mom, there's no evidence
against her!

326
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:16,500
No! That's enough!

327
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:18,800
I don't want to hear this
anymore, Red!

328
00:22:18,867 --> 00:22:20,033
Let's go home.

329
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:21,800
Stop! This is enough!

330
00:22:21,867 --> 00:22:24,000
Enough!

331
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:32,233
I feel like she loves Red
more than she loves me.

332
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:35,333
She didn't even think about
how I would feel.

333
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:38,433
But Amanda, you have to think
about her situation.

334
00:22:38,500 --> 00:22:41,233
They were on that island alone.

335
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:43,400
And they fell for each other.

336
00:22:43,467 --> 00:22:46,500
Not knowing that their parents
hate each other.

337
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:49,833
Why does it seem like
you know a lot?

338
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,000
I need to see Yenyen.

339
00:22:51,067 --> 00:22:52,433
Her mom might be hurting her.

340
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:53,567
You will forget about her
eventually.

341
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:55,400
- It will pass.
- Of course not!

342
00:22:55,467 --> 00:22:57,400
Sorry, but I can't let you
have your way this time.

343
00:22:57,467 --> 00:22:59,200
Red!

344
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:01,000
Red...

345
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:04,667
Mom, I'm so sorry.

346
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:08,567
Mom, I will do anything
you want.

347
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:11,233
I'll do whatever it takes
to make you forgive me.

348
00:23:11,300 --> 00:23:13,533
Stay away from Red.

349
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,200
Forget him.

350
00:23:15,267 --> 00:23:16,400
Red, why are you here?

351
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:18,133
You have to go. My mom might
wake up.

352
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,967
She'll be mad.

353
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,467
What is this boy doing here?

354
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:24,867
Do you want some of this?
Are you going to leave or not?

355
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:27,967
Are you going to leave or not?
